5. Saving the document does not make the squiggles go away, but moving the caret to the affected lined does (or causing any refresh of that part of the editor).

public class ConcreteClass extends AbstractClass {

    /*
    public void doStuff() {
    }
}

abstract class AbstractClass {
    public abstract void doStuff();
}

Sorry, two choices should be:
1. change default value of shrink from 'true' to 'false';
2. height takes higher priority than shrink.

What do you mean by a "customized menu item"?

The usual API for adding accelerator text to a menu item is to just add it to the menu text, following a tab character, in the setText method. JAWS will then speak the accelerator text just fine. For example:

MenuItem item = new MenuItem(fileMenu, SWT.NONE);
item.setText("&Save\tCtrl+S");
item.setAccelerator(SWT.CTRL + 'S');

